{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874976650,"sessionID":"ses_2859ad4c6ffeCrgVPMhIHvfDRB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a65a720001JjtDTBgUOzAhVQ","messageID":"msg_d7a659dbc001cvBeRGHITaNyQz","sessionID":"ses_2859ad4c6ffeCrgVPMhIHvfDRB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5e2e0d640eba4b38a7a14f0f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-030\n4: - **Module**: manifests\n5: - **Language**: YAML\n6: - **Size**: L\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: - **Stage**: ST-1\n9: \n10: ## 1. Architecture\n11: \n12: ### 1.1 Overview\n13: \n14: The AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\n15: \n16: ### 1.2 Chart Structure\n17: \n18: ```\n19: manifests/charts/base/\n20: ├── Chart.yaml\n21: ├── values.yaml\n22: ├── crds/\n23: │   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n24: │   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n25: └── templates/\n26:     ├── _helpers.tpl\n27:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n28:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n29:     ├── rbac/\n30:     │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n31:     │   └── router.yaml\n32:     └── volcano/\n33:         └── agent-scheduler.yaml\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### 1.3 Components\n37: \n38: | Component | Kind | Required | Description |\n39: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n40: | Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | Yes | Agent session management |\n41: | Router | Deployment + Service | Yes | API routing layer |\n42: | WorkloadManager RBAC | ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding | Yes | Cluster-wide permissions |\n43: | Router RBAC | ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding | Optional | Namespace-scoped permissions |\n44: | Volcano Scheduler | Multiple (SA, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) | Optional | Custom scheduler |\n45: | CRDs | CustomResourceDefinition | Yes | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n46: \n47: ## 2. Data Structures\n48: \n49: ### 2.1 Chart.yaml\n50: \n51: ```yaml\n52: apiVersion: v2\n53: name: agentcube\n54: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n55: type: application\n56: version: 0.1.0\n57: appVersion: 1.0.0\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ### 2.2 values.yaml Schema\n61: \n62: | Path | Type | Default | Required | Description |\n63: |------|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n64: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` | No | Image pull secrets |\n65: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` | No | Override chart name |\n66: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` | No | Override full name |\n67: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` | Yes | Redis address (host:port) |\n68: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` | No | Redis password |\n69: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Router replica count |\n70: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` | No | Router image |\n71: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n72: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n73: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` | No | Service type |\n74: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` | No | Service port |\n75: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` | No | Container port |\n76: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` | No | CPU limit |\n77: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` | No | Memory limit |\n78: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` | No | CPU request |\n79: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` | No | Memory request |\n80: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` | No | Additional env vars |\n81: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` | No | Service account name |\n82: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` | No | Create RBAC |\n83: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Replica count |\n84: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` | No | Image repository |\n85: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n86: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n87: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` | No | Service type |\n88: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` | No | Service port |\n89: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` | No | CPU limit |\n90: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` | No | Memory limit |\n91: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` | No | CPU request |\n92: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` | No | Memory request |\n93: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` | No | Additional env vars |\n94: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` | No | Enable scheduler |\n95: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Scheduler replicas |\n96: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` | No | Scheduler image |\n97: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n98: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n99: \n100: ## 3. API Contracts\n101: \n102: ### 3.1 Workload Manager Service\n103: \n104: ```yaml\n105: apiVersion: v1\n106: kind: Service\n107: metadata:\n108:   name: workloadmanager\n109:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n110: spec:\n111:   type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}\n112:   selector:\n113:     app: workloadmanager\n114:   ports:\n115:     - port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n116:       targetPort: http\n117:       protocol: TCP\n118:       name: http\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### 3.2 Workload Manager Deployment\n122: \n123: | Field | Source | Description |\n124: |-------|--------|-------------|\n125: | `replicas` | `.Values.workloadmanager.replicas` | Replica count |\n126: | `serviceAccountName` | `\"workloadmanager\"` | Fixed SA |\n127: | `image` | `.Values.workloadmanager.image.repository` + `:` + `.Values.workloadmanager.image.tag` | Container image |\n128: | `imagePullPolicy` | `.Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | Pull policy |\n129: | `env.REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Redis address |\n130: | `env.REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Redis password |\n131: | `env.AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `.Release.Namespace` | Release namespace |\n132: | `livenessProbe` | `/health` | Health endpoint |\n133: | `readinessProbe` | `/health` | Health endpoint |\n134: | `resources` | `.Values.workloadmanager.resources` | Resource limits |\n135: \n136: ### 3.3 Router Service\n137: \n138: ```yaml\n139: apiVersion: v1\n140: kind: Service\n141: metadata:\n142:   name: agentcube-router\n143:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n144: spec:\n145:   type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}\n146:   selector:\n147:     app: agentcube-router\n148:   ports:\n149:     - port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n150:       targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n151:       protocol: TCP\n152:       name: http\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### 3.4 Router Deployment\n156: \n157: | Field | Source | Description |\n158: |-------|--------|-------------|\n159: | `replicas` | `.Values.router.replicas` | Replica count |\n160: | `serviceAccountName` | `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` or `\"agentcube-router\"` | Conditional SA |\n161: | `image` | `.Values.router.image.repository` + `:` + `.Values.router.image.tag` | Container image |\n162: | `env.WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` | Internal URL |\n163: | `env.REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Redis address |\n164: | `env.REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Redis password |\n165: | `args` | `--debug` if `.Values.router.debug` | Debug flag |\n166: | `livenessProbe` | `/health/live` | Health endpoint |\n167: | `readinessProbe` | `/health/ready` | Health endpoint |\n168: \n169: ### 3.5 Workload Manager RBAC\n170: \n171: ```yaml\n172: apiVersion: v1\n173: kind: ServiceAccount\n174: metadata:\n175:   name: workloadmanager\n176:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n177: ---\n178: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n179: kind: ClusterRole\n180: metadata:\n181:   name: workloadmanager\n182: rules:\n183:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n184:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n185:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n186:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n187:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n188:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n189:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n190:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n191:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n192:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n193:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\", \"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n194:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"update\"]\n195:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n196:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\"]\n197:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n198:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n199:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n200:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 379. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-030\n- **Module**: manifests\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n- **Stage**: ST-1\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\n\n### 1.2 Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775874976633,"end":1775874976647}}}}
