{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775874982625,"sessionID":"ses_2859ad4c6ffeCrgVPMhIHvfDRB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a65c2df0015EvxteVSOszmZJ","messageID":"msg_d7a65bc6d001gFfV5zwPvNAeDs","sessionID":"ses_2859ad4c6ffeCrgVPMhIHvfDRB","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875032169,"sessionID":"ses_2859ad4c6ffeCrgVPMhIHvfDRB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a65c441001kzvZr1crzvOh4T","messageID":"msg_d7a65bc6d001gFfV5zwPvNAeDs","sessionID":"ses_2859ad4c6ffeCrgVPMhIHvfDRB","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_627f371113a24b88a5ab82d4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-032\n- **Module**: docker\n- **Language**: Dockerfile\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n- **Stage**: ST-1\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThis design implements multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, creating 3 optimized container images from a shared Go build infrastructure. The approach reduces image size by ~60-70% compared to single-stage builds and minimizes attack surface by excluding build tools from runtime images.\n\n### 1.2 Directory Structure\n\n```\ndocker/\n├── base.Dockerfile           # Shared Go build environment (builder stage)\n├── Dockerfile.router         # Router: builder → alpine runtime\n├── Dockerfile.workload-manager  # Workload Manager: builder → alpine runtime\n└── Dockerfile.agentd         # Agentd + Picod: builder → alpine runtime\n```\n\n### 1.3 Image Targets\n\n| Image | Binary | Builder Base | Runtime Base | Expected Size |\n|-------|--------|-------------|-------------|---------------|\n| `agentcube-router` | router | golang:1.24-alpine | alpine:3.19 | ~25-30MB |\n| `agentcube-workload-manager` | workload-manager | golang:1.24-alpine | alpine:3.19 | ~30-35MB |\n| `agentcube-agentd` | agentd + picod | golang:1.24-alpine | alpine:3.19 | ~35-40MB |\n\n### 1.4 Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n\nEach runtime Dockerfile uses a two-stage build pattern:\n\n```dockerfile\n# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /build\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /bin/[binary] ./cmd/[binary]\n\n# Stage 2: Runtime\nFROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 agentcube\nUSER 1000\nCOPY --from=builder /bin/[binary] /usr/local/bin/\nENTRYPOINT [\"/usr/local/bin/[binary]\"]\n```\n\n### 1.5 Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Docker Build Process                              │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                         │\n│  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐           │\n│  │ go.mod/go.sum│     │ go.mod/go.sum│     │ go.mod/go.sum│           │\n│  └──────┬───────┘     └──────┬───────┘     └──────┬───────┘           │\n│         │                    │                    │                    │\n│         ▼                    ▼                    ▼                    │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    base.Dockerfile (builder)                   │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder                      │   │   │\n│  │  │ WORKDIR /build                                          │   │   │\n│  │  │ COPY go.mod go.sum ./                                  │   │   │\n│  │  │ RUN go mod download                                    │   │   │\n│  │  │ COPY . .                                               │   │   │\n│  │  │ RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build ./cmd/...       │   │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│         │                    │                    │                    │\n│         ▼                    ▼                    ▼                    │\n│  ┌────────────┐        ┌────────────┐        ┌────────────┐              │\n│  │  router    │        │workload-   │        │  agentd    │              │\n│  │  binary    │        │  manager   │        │  + picod   │              │\n│  │            │        │  binary    │        │  binaries  │              │\n│  └─────┬──────┘        └─────┬──────┘        └─────┬──────┘              │\n│        │                     │                     │                    │\n│        ▼                     ▼                     ▼                    │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Runtime Images (alpine:3.19)                 │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐               │   │\n│  │  │agentcube-   │ │agentcube-   │ │agentcube-   │               │   │\n│  │  │  router    │ │workload-    │ │  agentd     │               │   │\n│  │  │  ~25MB     │ │  manager    │ │  ~40MB     │               │   │\n│  │  │             │ │  ~30MB      │ │             │               │   │\n│  │  └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘               │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                         │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Build Arguments\n\n| Arg | Default | Required | Description |\n|-----|---------|----------|-------------|\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | No | Go toolchain version |\n| `BUILDER_IMAGE` | `golang:1.24-alpine` | No | Build stage base image |\n| `RUNTIME_IMAGE` | `alpine:3.19` | No | Runtime stage base image |\n| `BINARY_VERSION` | `dev` | No | Binary version info |\n\n### 2.2 Build Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CGO_ENABLED` | Must be `0` for static linking |\n| `GOOS` | Must be `linux` for Linux containers |\n| `GOARCH` | Target architecture (default: amd64) |\n\n### 2.3 Runtime Configuration\n\n| Setting | Value | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| User | `agentcube` (UID 1000) | Non-root user for security |\n| Binary Location | `/usr/local/bin/` | Standard binary installation path |\n| Working Directory | `/home/agentcube` | User home directory |\n| Shell | `/bin/sh` | Alpine default shell |\n\n### 2.4 Binary Entry Points\n\n| Binary | Command | Arguments | Environment |\n|--------|---------|-----------|-------------|\n| router | `/usr/local/bin/router` | Flags from `cmd/router/main.go` | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `REDIS_ADDR` |\n| workload-manager | `/usr/local/bin/workload-manager` | Flags from `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD` |\n| agentd | `/usr/local/bin/agentd` | Flags from `cmd/agentd/main.go` | `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` |\n| picod | `/usr/local/bin/picod` | Flags from `cmd/picod/main.go` | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` |\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n# Build all images\ndocker-build: docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n\n# Build individual images\ndocker-build-router:\n\tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:latest .\n\ndocker-build-workload-manager:\n\tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:latest .\n\ndocker-build-agentd:\n\tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:latest .\n\n# Push images to registry\ndocker-push: docker-build\n\tdocker push agentcube-router:latest\n\tdocker push agentcube-workload-manager:latest\n\tdocker push agentcube-agentd:latest\n```\n\n### 3.2 Docker Build Commands\n\n```bash\n# Build with custom tags\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:v1.0.0 .\n\n# Build with build arguments\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n  --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.24 \\\n  --build-arg BINARY_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n  -t agentcube-router:latest .\n\n# Build with custom registry\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n  -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest .\n```\n\n### 3.3 Image Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# Verify binary executes\ndocker run --rm agentcube-router version\n\n# Verify non-root user\ndocker run --rm agentcube-router id\n\n# Check image layers\ndocker history agentcube-router:latest\n\n# Verify no source code in image\ndocker run --rm agentcube-router ls -la /home/agentcube\n\n# Check image size\ndocker images agentcube-router\n```\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Build Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `go: cannot find main module` | Missing go.mod in context | Ensure build context is project root |\n| `cannot find module` | go.sum mismatch | Run `go mod download` before build |\n| `cannot build binary` | Missing cmd path | Verify cmd/{binary}/main.go exists |\n| `stat binary: no such file` | Build failed silently | Check for compilation errors |\n\n### 4.2 Runtime Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `binary not found` | Incorrect COPY path | Verify binary path in Dockerfile |\n| `permission denied` | Binary not executable | Add chmod +x in Dockerfile |\n| `no such file or directory` | Missing libc | Use `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n\n### 4.3 Multi-Stage Build Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `COPY --from: no such image` | Stage name typo | Verify stage names match |\n| `stage 'builder' not found` | Incorrect stage reference | Use `--target` flag |\n\n### 4.4 Build Validation\n\n```bash\n# Pre-build validation\nvalidate-dockerfiles:\n\t@echo \"Validating Dockerfiles...\"\n\t@docker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder --no-run .\n\t@echo \"Dockerfiles are valid\"\n\n# Post-build validation\nvalidate-images: docker-build\n\t@docker run --rm agentcube-router --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Router binary failed\" && exit 1)\n\t@docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Workload-manager binary failed\" && exit 1)\n\t@docker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Agentd binary failed\" && exit 1)\n\t@docker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help > /dev/null || (echo \"Picod binary failed\" && exit 1)\n\t@echo \"All images validated\"\n```\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\nBuild verification tests for each Dockerfile:\n\n```bash\n# Test base Dockerfile\ndocker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder -t agentcube-builder:test .\n\n# Test individual Dockerfiles\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:test .\ndocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:test .\n```\n\n### 5.2 Binary Execution Tests\n\n| Test | Command | Expected |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| Router version | `docker run --rm agentcube-router version` | Exit 0, output version |\n| Router help | `docker run --rm agentcube-router --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n| WM help | `docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n| Agentd help | `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n| Picod help | `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help` | Exit 0, show help |\n\n### 5.3 Security Tests\n\n| Test | Command | Expected |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| Non-root user | `docker run --rm agentcube-router id` | UID 1000, not 0 |\n| No source code | `docker run --rm agentcube-router ls /build` | Error/not found |\n| No go.mod | `docker run --rm agentcube-router cat go.mod` | Error/not found |\n| Minimal packages | `docker run --rm agentcube-router apk list` | Alpine base only |\n\n### 5.4 Size Tests\n\n| Test | Command | Expected |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| Router size | `docker images agentcube-router --format \"{{.Size}}\"` | < 50MB |\n| Workload-manager size | `docker images agentcube-workload-manager --format \"{{.Size}}\"` | < 50MB |\n| Agentd size | `docker images agentcube-agentd --format \"{{.Size}}\"` | < 60MB |\n\n### 5.5 Cache Reuse Tests\n\n```bash\n# First build (cold)\ntime docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .\n\n# Second build (warm, no changes)\ntime docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .\n\n# Verify cache used\n# Expected: Second build should complete in < 30 seconds\n```\n\n### 5.6 End-to-End Tests\n\n```bash\n# Integration test script\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\necho \"Building images...\"\nmake docker-build\n\necho \"Testing image sizes...\"\nfor img in router workload-manager agentd; do\n    size=$(docker images agentcube-$img --format \"{{.Size}}\" | sed 's/MB//')\n    if (( $(echo \"$size > 60\" | bc -l) )); then\n        echo \"FAIL: agentcube-$img exceeds size limit: $size MB\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    echo \"PASS: agentcube-$img size: $size MB\"\ndone\n\necho \"Testing binary execution...\"\ndocker run --rm agentcube-router version\ndocker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help\ndocker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help\ndocker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help\n\necho \"Testing non-root execution...\"\ndocker run --rm agentcube-router id | grep \"uid=1000\"\n\necho \"All tests passed!\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/\n- Alpine Linux container best practices: https://wiki.alpinelinux.org/wiki/Docker\n- Go static builds: https://github.com/golang/go/wiki/GoReleaser\n- Delta spec: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-032/proposal.md`\n- Helm chart (AR-030): `manifests/agentcube/values.yaml`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/design.md","time":{"start":1775875032158,"end":1775875032167}}}}
